    "department": "Revenue",
    "description": "ABOUT NEON\n\nNeon is a global payments and e-commerce platform designed to help game publishers earn more money and independence from app stores. We believe commerce should be open and transparent: clear decisions, actionable insights, and aligned incentives. Founded by payments, fintech and gaming veterans, Neon focuses on product and partnership excellence: we share the playbook, co-pilot decisions, and abstract away risk and complexity for our customers. We’re replacing old-school, black-box relics with clear, modern, and developer-centric infrastructure.\n\nAs an early team member, you’ll have the opportunity to shape and scale Neon’s product and culture, making a direct impact on our growth and success. You’ll join a collaborative, diverse team from world-class companies like Apple, Affirm, Unity, and Visa, backed by renowned VC's including Thrive, a16z, Griffin Gaming, Ribbit, and Renegade. If you want to build disruptive technology, challenge the status quo, and help game creators thrive on their own terms, read on.\n\nAbout the Role\n\nNeon is looking for a strategic, highly organized, and analytical Lead Product Marketing Manager to serve as the foundational pillar of our marketing team. Additionally, you will own our brand identity and content engine.\n\nThe ideal candidate is a \"full-stack\" marketer who can alternate between high-level strategic planning and hands-on execution. You are a master of cross-functional orchestration, able to align Product, Sales, Customer Success, and Engineering teams to deliver a cohesive narrative to our customers.\n\nWhat You’ll Do (Responsibilities)\n\n - Strategic GTM Leadership: Define and execute the end-to-end Go-To-Market (GTM) strategy for Neon’s suite of payment and gaming tools. Act as the primary marketing stakeholder in leadership discussions.\n\n - Product Messaging \u0026 Positioning: Develop a deep understanding of our product capabilities and the competitive landscape + industry trends to create compelling narratives that resonate with game developers and publishers.\n\n - Sales Enablement \u0026 Tooling: Lead the creation of high-impact sales materials (decks, one-pagers, case studies) and training sessions to accelerate the sales cycle.\n\n - Cross-Functional Orchestration: Serve as the \"connective tissue\" between Product, Sales, and Customer Success. Ensure all teams are armed with the right messaging, collateral, and market insights.\n\n - Analytical Rigor: Establish success metrics for marketing initiatives. Use data to track performance, identify market opportunities, and iterate on our growth strategy.\n\nWhat You’ll Bring (Requirements)\n\n - 7+ Years of Experience: Proven track record in Product Marketing, preferably within B2B SaaS, Fintech, or the Gaming industry. Experience in a \"founding\" or \"lead\" marketing role is a major plus.\n\n - Strategic \u0026 Analytical Mindset: You don't just execute; you ask \"why.\" You are comfortable using data to back up your decisions and can translate complex technical features into clear value propositions.\n\n - Exceptional Organization: You are a natural project manager. You can juggle multiple high-priority launches and workstreams without dropping the ball.\n\n - Strong XFN Influence: You have a demonstrated ability to lead and influence senior stakeholders across Engineering, Product, and Sales.\n\n - Storytelling Excellence: You are a gifted writer and communicator. You can craft a narrative that is both emotionally engaging and functionally precise.\n\n - Adaptability: You thrive in an environment where you may need to pivot from a deep-dive product launch to a brand-awareness social campaign in the same day.\n\n - Entrepreneurial Spirit: You are comfortable with ambiguity and excited by the challenge of building a marketing function from the ground up.\n\nBonus Points\n\n - Experience in the gaming space.\n\n - Previous experience working in a high-growth startup environment.\n\n - Previous experience in content marketing or brand management.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
